《'''手中纸，心中爱'''》（{{lang-en|''The Paper Menagerie''}}）为[[刘宇昆|刘宇昆]]在2011年发表的一篇[[科幻小说|科幻小说]]。首次发表于《{{Translink|en|The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction|4=幻想与科幻杂志}}》中。小说讲述了一位中国母亲和她在美国出生的儿子之间的关系与冲突<ref>{{Cite web|title=Read Ken Liu's Hugo, Nebula, and World Fantasy Award-winning 'The Paper Menagerie'|url=https://www.theverge.com/2012/11/18/3658698/read-ken-liu-paper-menagerie|accessdate=2021-01-05|date=2012-11-18|last=Robertson|first=Adi|work=The Verge|language=en|archive-date=2016-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324101846/https://www.theverge.com/2012/11/18/3658698/read-ken-liu-paper-menagerie|dead-url=no}}</ref>，用[[魔幻现实主义|魔幻现实主义]]的手法表现[[亚裔美国人|亚裔美国人]]艰难处境<ref name="#1">{{Cite web|title=Review: ‘The Paper Menagerie’ is a must read for Asian Americans|url=https://highschool.latimes.com/orange-county-school-of-the-arts/review-the-paper-menagerie-is-a-must-read-for-asian-americans/|accessdate=2021-01-05|date=2020-05-27|last=WongMay 27|first=Katherine|work=HS Insider|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121191413/https://highschool.latimes.com/orange-county-school-of-the-arts/review-the-paper-menagerie-is-a-must-read-for-asian-americans/|dead-url=no}}</ref>和情感隔阂<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=《三体》《北京折叠》译者刘宇昆:两次获得"雨果奖"|url=http://culture.people.com.cn/n1/2016/0831/c22219-28679601.html|accessdate=2021-01-05|author=华西都市报|date=|format=|work=|publisher=人民网|language=zh-CN|archive-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126080724/http://culture.people.com.cn/n1/2016/0831/c22219-28679601.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。该小说获得了[[星云奖|星云奖]]、[[雨果奖|雨果奖]]和[[世界奇幻奖|世界奇幻奖]]。<ref name="#2">{{Cite web|title=Read Ken Liu's amazing story that swept the Hugo, Nebula and World Fantasy Awards|url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/read-ken-lius-amazing-story-that-swept-the-hugo-nebula-5958919|accessdate=2021-01-05|author=|date=|format=|work=io9|publisher=|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308150200/https://io9.gizmodo.com/read-ken-lius-amazing-story-that-swept-the-hugo-nebula-5958919|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 内容简介 ==
杰克小时候非常喜欢他妈妈给他折的老虎[[折纸|折纸]]。当他吹动折纸后，这些动物折纸会如获生命般地动起来。当他成长为青少年以后，由于对[[种族主义|亚裔的歧视]]，他逐渐疏远母亲和这些动物折纸。在他母亲逝世两年后，他找回了小时候的折纸，并在母亲的一封信中了解到了他母亲的过去。

== 反响与评价 ==
《手中纸，心中爱》获得了2012年星云奖最佳短篇小说<ref>{{Cite web|title=sfadb: Nebula Awards 2012|url=http://www.sfadb.com/Nebula_Awards_2012|accessdate=2021-01-05|work=www.sfadb.com|archive-date=2013-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922062449/http://www.sfadb.com/Nebula_Awards_2012|dead-url=no}}</ref>、雨果奖最佳短篇小说<ref>{{Cite web|title=2012 Hugo Awards|url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2012-hugo-awards/|accessdate=2021-01-05|date=2012-04-07|work=The Hugo Awards|language=en|archive-date=2012-04-09|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66nnsGGRI?url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2012-hugo-awards/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、世界奇幻奖最佳短篇小说<ref>{{Cite web|title=sfadb: World Fantasy Awards 2012|url=http://www.sfadb.com/World_Fantasy_Awards_2012|accessdate=2021-01-05|work=www.sfadb.com|archive-date=2014-03-14|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6O4greCEy?url=http://www.sfadb.com/World_Fantasy_Awards_2012|dead-url=no}}</ref>，这是世界上第一部同时获得上述三个奖的作品<ref name="#2"/>。刘宇昆也因此成为了第一位获得星云奖和雨果奖两项世界科幻小说大奖的华裔作家。<ref name="雅虎">{{cite web|title=华裔作家斩获科幻界诺贝尔奖 科幻也能写真情|url=http://cul.cn.yahoo.com/ypen/20120905/1293286.html|accessdate=2011-09-07|author=钱江晚报|date=2012-09-05|format=|publisher=雅虎|language=zh-cn|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121029171843/http://cul.cn.yahoo.com/ypen/20120905/1293286.html|archivedate=2012-10-29|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

劉宇昆形容自己的写作手法為「隱喻實物化」。在该小说中的摺紙老虎，比喻主角母親的对儿子的爱，在小说里劉宇昆以超現實手法将其寫得如同真的动物一般。<ref>{{Cite web|title=【專訪】科幻作家劉宇昆：我其實是史學家 研究的是神話|url=https://www.hk01.com/藝文/136789/專訪-科幻作家劉宇昆-我其實是史學家-研究的是神話|accessdate=2021-01-05|author=|date=2017-11-28|last=香港01評論|format=|work=香港01|publisher=|language=zh-HK|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106195420/https://www.hk01.com/%E8%97%9D%E6%96%87/136789/%E5%B0%88%E8%A8%AA-%E7%A7%91%E5%B9%BB%E4%BD%9C%E5%AE%B6%E5%8A%89%E5%AE%87%E6%98%86-%E6%88%91%E5%85%B6%E5%AF%A6%E6%98%AF%E5%8F%B2%E5%AD%B8%E5%AE%B6-%E7%A0%94%E7%A9%B6%E7%9A%84%E6%98%AF%E7%A5%9E%E8%A9%B1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[NPR|NPR]]评论认为，此作品让人产生了从未有过的感动。<ref>{{Cite web|title=No Paper Tiger, This 'Menagerie' Is Full Of Fierce Feeling|url=https://www.npr.org/2016/03/13/468942030/no-paper-tiger-this-menagerie-is-full-of-fierce-feeling|accessdate=2021-01-05|author=Amal El-Mohtar|date=|format=|work=|publisher=NPR|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210212174404/https://www.npr.org/2016/03/13/468942030/no-paper-tiger-this-menagerie-is-full-of-fierce-feeling|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉矶时报]]》评论认为：“所有人，尤其是亚裔美国人都应该阅读此作品。”<ref name="#1"/>《[[华西都市报|华西都市报]]》认为作者用科幻探讨了每个人年少时都曾犯下的错误，表达了“情感是根植于语言之上”的哲理。<ref name=":0" />

